      "message": "nit: This is slightly different logic than in the previous patch set. Was: ignore context errors as long as we\u0027ve got a final build somehow. Now: if the context dies concurrently with ending build, the result depends on an outcome of a race. I like the previous one better (more deterministic in a way). I think it will make code slightly shorter too, in exchange for an ugly hack:\n\nin mkBuildbucketBuffer:\n\nif final {\n  if err !\u003d nil {\n    finalErr.Store(err)\n  } else {\n    finalErr.Store(errSuccess) // ugh\n  }\n}\n\nhere:\n\nif err, _ :\u003d finalErr.Load().(error); err !\u003d nil {\n  if err \u003d\u003d errSuccess {\n    return nil\n  }\n  return err\n}\nreturn errors.New(\"final build was never processed\")",
